<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<qti-assessment-item
    xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0p1_v1p0.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/mathml/v3p0/schema/xsd/mathml3.xsd"
    identifier="parabola-vertex-coordinates"
    title="Coordinates of a Parabola's Vertex"
    time-dependent="false"
    xml:lang="en-US">

    <qti-response-declaration base-type="identifier" cardinality="single" identifier="RESPONSE">
        <qti-correct-response>
            <qti-value>B</qti-value>
        </qti-correct-response>
    </qti-response-declaration>

    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>

    <qti-item-body>
        <p>The graph of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is a downward-opening parabola whose vertex is at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>
        <div id="reference_text">
            <img src="https://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-graphie/71814476610d1ed8a4e30e69e329b9ba02c0f4c9.svg" alt="Function f is graphed. The graph is a downward-opening parabola with its vertex at (-3, 4), and it passes through the points (-5, 0) and (-1, 0)."/>
        </div>
        <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
            <qti-prompt>Which of the following points is the vertex of the parabola?</qti-prompt>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="A">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="A">This point is a zero (x-intercept) of the graph.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="B">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="B">The vertex is the point on the parabola where the graph changes from increasing to decreasing or vice versa. The graph changes from increasing to decreasing at the point <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="C">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="C">This point is a zero (x-intercept) of the graph.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="D">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="D">This point is the y-intercept of the graph.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
        </qti-choice-interaction>
        
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="CORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> The vertex at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math> is the highest point on this downward-opening parabola, where the graph changes from increasing to decreasing.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="INCORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Not quite.</strong> The vertex of a parabola is its turning pointâ€”the highest point for a downward-opening parabola or the lowest point for an upward-opening parabola. For this downward-opening parabola, look for the highest point, which is at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
    </qti-item-body>

    <qti-response-processing template="https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/rptemplates/match_correct"/>

</qti-assessment-item>